Life Hack 1

Use this structure for all segment tree problems after writing this structure from scratch and understanding what this structure does (check the video class to understand more):

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 3e5 + 9;

int a[N];
struct ST {
  int t[4 * N];
  static const int inf = 1e9;
  ST() {
    memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
  }
  void build(int n, int b, int e) {
    if (b == e) {
      t[n] = a[b];
      return;
    }
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
    build(l, b, mid);
    build(r, mid + 1, e);
    t[n] = max(t[l], t[r]); // change this
  }
  void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
    if (b > i || e < i) return;
    if (b == e && b == i) {
      t[n] = x; // update
      return;
    }
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
    upd(l, b, mid, i, x);
    upd(r, mid + 1, e, i, x);
    t[n] = max(t[l], t[r]); // change this
  }
  int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
    if (b > j || e < i) return -inf; // return appropriate value
    if (b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
    return max(query(l, b, mid, i, j), query(r, mid + 1, e, i, j)); // change this
  }
}t;

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n = 5;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    a[i] = i;
  }
  t.build(1, 1, n); // building the segment tree
  t.upd(1, 1, n, 2, 10); // assiging 10 to the index 2 (a[2] := 10)
  cout << t.query(1, 1, n, 1, 5) << '\n'; // range max query on the segment [1, 5]

  return 0;
}

Life Hack 2

Use this structure for all segment tree lazy problems after writing this structure from scratch and understanding what this structure does (check the video class to understand more):

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 5e5 + 9;
int a[N];
struct ST {
  #define lc (n << 1)
  #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
  long long t[4 * N], lazy[4 * N];
  ST() {
    memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    memset(lazy, 0, sizeof lazy);
  }
  inline void push(int n, int b, int e) { // change this
    if (lazy[n] == 0) return;
    t[n] = t[n] + lazy[n] * (e - b + 1);
    if (b != e) {
      lazy[lc] = lazy[lc] + lazy[n];
      lazy[rc] = lazy[rc] + lazy[n];
    }
    lazy[n] = 0;
  }
  inline long long combine(long long a,long long b) { // change this
    return a + b;
  }
  inline void pull(int n) { // change this
    t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];
  }
  void build(int n, int b, int e) {
    lazy[n] = 0; // change this
    if (b == e) {
      t[n] = a[b];
      return;
    }
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
    build(lc, b, mid);
    build(rc, mid + 1, e);
    pull(n);
  }
  void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, long long v) {
    push(n, b, e);
    if (j < b || e < i) return;
    if (i <= b && e <= j) {
      lazy[n] = v; //set lazy
      push(n, b, e);
      return;
    }
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
    upd(lc, b, mid, i, j, v);
    upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, v);
    pull(n);
  }
  long long query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
    push(n, b, e);
    if (i > e || b > j) return 0; //return null
    if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
    return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
  }
}t;
int32_t main() {
  int n = 5;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    a[i] = i;
  }
  t.build(1, 1, n); // building the segment tree
  t.upd(1, 1, n, 2, 3, 10); // adding 10 to the segment [2, 3]
  cout << t.query(1, 1, n, 1, 5) << '\n'; // range sum query on the segment [1, 5]
  return 0;
}

#include<bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace __gnu_pbds;
using namespace std;

template <typename T> using o_set = tree<T, null_type, less<T>, rb_tree_tag, tree_order_statistics_node_update>;

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  o_set<int> se;
  se.insert(4);
  se.insert(2);
  se.insert(5);
  // sorted set se = [2, 4, 5]
  cout << se.order_of_key(5) << '\n'; // number of elements < 5

Offline Queries

"If a problem involve processing queries then there are online solutions and offline solutions. Online means that your solution can process each query before reading the the queries that come after it. Offline means that your solution reads all queries then process them , probably you sort the queries in some order so that you can process them faster." - Hasan Jaddouh

Solve the following problem to understand better.

Problem: Given an array of length n105n \le 10^5n105 and q105q \le 10^5q105 queries. In each query you need to find the number of distinct elements in a subarray.

Problem link: smash me

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  vector<int> a(n + 1);
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
  }
  int q; cin >> q;
  vector<int> ans(q + 1);
  vector<pair<int, int>> Q[n + 1];
  for (int i = 1; i <= q; i++) {
    int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
    Q[r].push_back({l, i});
  }
  // build a segment tree where every value is 0
  map<int, int> last_id;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    upd(i, 1); // add 1 to the ith index
    if (last_id.find(a[i]) != last_id.end()) {
      upd(last_id[a[i]], -1); // add -1 to the last index having value a[i]
    }
    last_id[a[i]] = i;
    for (auto x: Q[i]) {
      int l = x.first, id = x.second;
      ans[id] = query(l, i); // sum of l to the ith index
    }
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= q; i++) {
    cout << ans[i] << '\n';
  }
  return 0;
}

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long

const int N = 2e5 + 9;
int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    ll t[4 * N];
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline ll combine(ll a, ll b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = 0;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    ll query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	unordered_map<int, int> mp;
	vector<int> v;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		cin >> a[i];
		v.push_back(a[i]);
	}
	sort(v.begin(), v.end());
	int k = 1;
	for(auto x: v) mp[x] = k++;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	ll ans = 0;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		ans += t.query(1, 1, n, mp[a[i]] + 1, n);
		t.upd(1, 1, n, mp[a[i]], 1);
	}
	cout << ans << '\n';
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    cin >> tt;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

#define ll long long

const int N = 1e6 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    ll t[4 * N];
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline ll combine(ll a, ll b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = 0;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    ll query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	unordered_map<int, int> mp;
	vector<int> v;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		cin >> a[i];
		v.push_back(a[i]);
	}
	sort(v.begin(), v.end());
	int k = 1;
	for(auto x: v) mp[x] = k++;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	ll ans = 0;
	o_set<int> st;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		int h = mp[a[i]];
		int grt = st.size() - st.order_of_key(h);
		t.upd(1, 1, n, h, grt);
		ans += t.query(1, 1, n, h + 1, n);
		st.insert(h);
	}
	cout << ans << '\n';
}

3. Problem C

Editorial: link

Code(C++) [using Segment Tree] 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long

const int N = 2e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline int combine(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = 0;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] += x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	string s;
	cin >> s;
	string rs;
	rs = s;
	reverse(rs.begin(), rs.end());
	queue<int> mp[26];
	int k = 1;
	for(auto c: rs) {
		mp[c - 'a'].push(k++);
	}
	for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
		a[i] = mp[s[i] - 'a'].front();
		mp[s[i] - 'a'].pop();
	}
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	ll ans = 0;
	for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
		t.upd(1, 1, n, a[i], +1);
		ans += (ll)t.query(1, 1, n, a[i] + 1, n);
	}
	cout << ans << '\n';
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> tt;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }
return 0;
}

4. Problem D

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	int t[4 * N], lazy[4 * N];
	ST() {
		memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
		memset(lazy, 0, sizeof lazy);
	}
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) { 
		if (lazy[n] == 0) return;
		t[n] = (e - b + 1) - t[n];
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] ^= 1;
			lazy[rc] ^= 1;
		}
		lazy[n] = 0;
	}
	inline int combine(int a, int b) { 
	 	return a + b;
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = 0;
		if (b == e) {
			t[n] = a[b];
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] ^= 1;
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j);
		pull(n);
	}
	int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return 0;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
	string s;
	cin >> s;
	int n = (int)s.size();
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		a[i] = s[i-1] - '0';
	}
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	int q;
	cin >> q;
	while(q--) {
		char ch; cin >> ch;
		if(ch == 'I') {
			int x, y; cin >> x >> y;
			t.upd(1, 1, n, x, y);
		}
		else {
			int x; cin >> x;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, x, x) << '\n';
		}
	}
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    cin >> tt;
    int cs = 1;
    while(tt--) {
    	cout << "Case " << cs++ << ":" << '\n';
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

5. Problem E

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) {
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline int combine(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] += x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, q;
	cin >> n >> q;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	while(q--) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if(x == 1) {
			int y; cin >> y;
			int v = t.query(1, 1, n, y + 1, y + 1);
			cout << v << '\n';
			t.upd(1, 1, n, y + 1, -v);
		}
		else if(x == 2) {
			int y, v; cin >> y >> v;

		}
		else {
			int y, z; cin >> y >> z;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, y + 1, z + 1) << '\n';
		}
	}
}

6. Problem F

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define ll long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct Node {
	Node(bool ig = false) {
		ignore = ig;
	}
	bool ignore;
	pair<int, int> lmx, rmx, mx;
};

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    Node t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;

    inline void pull(int n) {
        if(t[lc].lmx.ss == t[lc].rmx.ss && t[lc].rmx.ss == t[rc].lmx.ss) {
  			t[n].lmx = {t[lc].lmx.ff + t[rc].lmx.ff, t[lc].lmx.ss};
  		}
  		else{
       		t[n].lmx = t[lc].lmx;
  		}
        if(t[lc].rmx.ss == t[rc].lmx.ss && t[rc].lmx.ss == t[rc].rmx.ss) {
        	t[n].rmx = {t[lc].rmx.ff + t[rc].rmx.ff , t[lc].rmx.ss};
        }
        else {
        	t[n].rmx = t[rc].rmx;
        }
        t[n].mx = max(t[lc].mx, t[rc].mx);
        if(t[lc].rmx.ss == t[rc].lmx.ss) {
        	t[n].mx = max({t[n].mx, {t[lc].rmx.ff + t[rc].lmx.ff, t[lc].rmx.ss}, t[n].lmx, t[n].rmx});
        } 
    }
    inline Node combine(Node a, Node b) {
    	if(b.ignore && !a.ignore) return a;
    	if(a.ignore && !b.ignore) return b;
    	if(a.ignore && b.ignore) return Node(true);
       	Node c;
  		if(a.lmx.ss == a.rmx.ss && a.rmx.ss == b.lmx.ss) {
  			c.lmx = {a.lmx.ff + b.lmx.ff, a.lmx.ss};
  		}
  		else{
       		c.lmx = a.lmx;
  		}
        if(a.rmx.ss == b.lmx.ss && b.lmx.ss == b.rmx.ss) {
        	c.rmx = {a.rmx.ff + b.rmx.ff , a.rmx.ss};
        }
        else {
        	c.rmx = b.rmx;
        }
        c.mx = max(a.mx, b.mx);
        if(a.rmx.ss == b.lmx.ss) {
        	c.mx = max({c.mx, {a.rmx.ff + b.lmx.ff, a.rmx.ss}, c.lmx, c.rmx});
        }
        return c;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n].lmx = {1, a[b]};
            t[n].rmx = {1, a[b]};
            t[n].mx = {1, a[b]};
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    
    Node query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return Node(true);
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        Node temp = combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
        return temp;
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, c, q;
	cin >> n >> c >> q;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	while(q--) {
		int x, y;
		cin >> x >> y;
		cout << t.query(1, 1, n, x, y).mx.ff << '\n';
	}
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    cin >> tt;
    int cs = 1;
    while(tt--) {
    	cout << "Case " << cs++ << ":" << '\n';
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

7. Problem G

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define ll long long

const int N = 2e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline int combine(int a, int b) { 
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = 0; 
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] += x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0; 
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, q;
	cin >> n >> q;
	vector<pair<int, int>> input;
	vector<int> dt;
	for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
		int x, y;
		cin >> x >> y;
		dt.push_back(x);
		dt.push_back(y);
		input.push_back({x, y});
	}
	vector<int> points;
	for(int i = 0; i < q; i++) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		points.push_back(x);
		dt.push_back(x);
	}
	sort(dt.begin(), dt.end());
	unordered_map<int, int> mp;
	int k = 1;
	for(auto x: dt) {
		if(mp[x] == 0) mp[x] = k++;
	}
	int nn = k - 1;
	t.build(1, 1, nn);
	vector<pair<int, int>> segs;
	for(auto x: input) {
		segs.push_back({mp[x.ff], 0});
		segs.push_back({mp[x.ss], 2});
	}
	for(auto x: points) segs.push_back({mp[x], 1});
	sort(segs.begin(), segs.end());
	int ans[nn + 1];
	memset(ans, 0, sizeof ans);
	for(int i = 0; i < segs.size(); i++) {
		auto x = segs[i];
		if(x.ss == 0) {
			t.upd(1, 1, nn, x.ff, 1);
		}
		else if(x.ss == 1) {
			ans[x.ff] = t.query(1, 1, nn, 1, x.ff);
		}
		else {
			t.upd(1, 1, nn, x.ff, -1);
		}
	}
	for(auto x: points) {
		cout << ans[mp[x]] << '\n';
	}	
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    cin >> tt;
    int cs = 1;
    while(tt--) {
    	cout << "Case " << cs++ << ":" << '\n';
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

8. Problem H

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define ll long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct Node {
	int zero, one, two;
	Node() {
		zero = 0, one = 0, two = 0;
	}
	Node operator+ (const Node& node) {
		Node ans;
		ans.zero = zero + node.zero;
		ans.one = one + node.one;
		ans.two = two + node.two;
		return ans;
	}
};

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	Node t[4 * N];
	int lazy[4 * N];
	
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) {
		if (lazy[n] % 3 == 0) {
			lazy[n] = 0;
			return;
		}
		int add = lazy[n] % 3;
		if(add == 1) {
			int tz = t[n].zero, to = t[n].one;
			t[n].zero = t[n].two;
			t[n].one = tz;
			t[n].two = to;
		}
		else {
			int tz = t[n].zero;
			t[n].zero = t[n].one;
			t[n].one = t[n].two;
			t[n].two = tz;
		}
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] += add;
			lazy[rc] += add;
		}
		lazy[n] = 0;
	}
	inline Node combine(Node a, Node b) {
	 	return a + b;
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = 0; 
		if (b == e) {
			t[n].zero = 1;
			t[n].one = 0;
			t[n].two = 0;
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] += 1;
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j);
		pull(n);
	}
	Node query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return Node();
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, q;
	cin >> n >> q;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	while(q--) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if(x == 0) {
			int i, j; cin >> i >> j;
			t.upd(1, 1, n, i + 1, j + 1);
		}
		else {
			int i, j; cin >> i >> j;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, i + 1, j + 1).zero << '\n';
		}
	}
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    cin >> tt;
    int cs = 1;
    while(tt--) {
    	cout << "Case " << cs++ << ":" << '\n';
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

9. Problem I

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define int long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct Node {
	int lmx, rmx, mx, sum;
	Node() {
		lmx = rmx = mx = -INT_MAX;
		sum = 0;
	}
};

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    Node t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
       	t[n].mx = max({t[lc].mx, t[rc].mx, t[lc].rmx + t[rc].lmx});
       	t[n].lmx = max(t[lc].lmx, t[lc].sum + t[rc].lmx);
       	t[n].rmx = max(t[rc].rmx, t[rc].sum + t[lc].rmx);
       	t[n].sum = t[lc].sum + t[rc].sum;
    }
    inline Node combine(Node a, Node b) {
    	Node c;
        c.mx = max({a.mx, b.mx, a.rmx + b.lmx});
       	c.lmx = max(a.lmx, a.sum + b.lmx);
       	c.rmx = max(b.rmx, b.sum + a.rmx);
       	c.sum = a.sum + b.sum;
       	return c;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n].lmx = a[b];
            t[n].rmx = a[b];
            t[n].mx = a[b];
            t[n].sum = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n].lmx = x;
            t[n].rmx = x;
            t[n].mx = x;
            t[n].sum = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    Node query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return Node();
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	int q; cin >> q;
	while(q--) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if(x == 0) {
			int i, j; cin >> i >> j;
			t.upd(1, 1, n, i, j);
		}
		else {
			int i, j; cin >> i >> j;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, i, j).mx << '\n';
		}
	}
}

10. Problem J

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define int long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct Node {
	int bits[20];
	int sum;
	Node() {
		memset(bits, 0, sizeof bits);
		sum = 0;
	}
	Node operator+ (const Node& node) {
		Node ans;
		for(int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
			ans.bits[i] = bits[i] + node.bits[i];
		}
		ans.sum = 0;
		for(int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
			ans.sum += ans.bits[i] * (1 << i);
		}
		return ans;
	}
};

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	Node t[4 * N];
	int lazy[4 * N];
	
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) {
		if (lazy[n] == 0) return;
		for(int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
			if(lazy[n] & (1 << i)) {
				t[n].bits[i] = (e - b + 1) - t[n].bits[i];
				t[n].sum = 0;
				for(int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
					t[n].sum += t[n].bits[i] * (1 << i);
				}
			}
		}
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] ^= lazy[n];
			lazy[rc] ^= lazy[n];
		}
		lazy[n] = 0;
	}
	inline Node combine(Node a,Node b) {
	 	return a + b;
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = 0;
		if (b == e) {
			for(int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
				t[n].bits[i] = (a[b] & (1 << i)) ? 1 : 0;
				t[n].sum = a[b];
			}
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, int v) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] = v;
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j, v);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, v);
		pull(n);
	}
	Node query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return Node();
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	int q; cin >> q;
	while(q--) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if(x == 1) {
			int i, j; cin >> i >> j;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, i, j).sum << '\n';
		}
		else {
			int i, j, v; cin >> i >> j >> v;
			t.upd(1, 1, n, i, j, v);
		}
	}
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> tt;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }

return 0;

11. Problem K

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { 
        t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];  
    }
    inline int combine(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = 0;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] += x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }

void solve() {
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	int q; cin >> q;
	vector<int> ques[30001];
	map<pair<int, int>, int> ans;
	vector<pair<int, int>> inputs;
	while(q--) {
		int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
		inputs.push_back({l, r});
		ans[{l, r}] = 0;
		ques[r].push_back(l);
	}
	map<int, int> last_id;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		if(last_id.find(a[i]) != last_id.end()) {
			t.upd(1, 1, n, last_id[a[i]], -1);
		}
		last_id[a[i]] = i;
		t.upd(1, 1, n, i, +1); 
		for(auto x: ques[i]) {
			ans[{x, i}] = t.query(1, 1, n, x, i);
		}
	}
	for(auto x: inputs) {
		cout << ans[x] << '\n';
	}
}

        pull(n);
    }
    ll query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, q;
	cin >> n >> q;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	unordered_map<int, int> index;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		cin >> a[i];
		index[a[i]] = i;
	}
	vector<int> div_pairs[n + 1];
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		for(int j = i; j <= n; j += i) {
			int x = index[i], y = index[j];
			div_pairs[max(x, y)].push_back(min(x, y));
		}
	}
	vector<pair<int, int>> ques[n + 1];
	int k = 0;
	while(q--) {
		int l, r;
		cin >> l >> r;
		ques[r].push_back({l, k++});
	}
	ll ans[k];
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		for(auto x: div_pairs[i]) {
			t.upd(1, 1, n, x, +1);
		}
		for(auto x: ques[i]) {
			ans[x.ss] = t.query(1, 1, n, x.ff, i);
		}
	}
	for(int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
		cout << ans[i] << '\n';
	}
}

	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n, int level) {
        t[n] = ((pn - level) & 1) ? (t[lc] ^ t[rc]) : (t[lc] | t[rc]);  
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e, int level) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid, level + 1);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e, level + 1);
        pull(n, level);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x, int level) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x, level + 1);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x, level + 1);
        pull(n, level);
    }
}t;

14. Problem N

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define int long long

const int N = 2e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    pair<int, int> t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    
    inline void pull(int n) {
   		t[n].ff = max(t[lc].ff, t[rc].ff);
   		t[n].ss = t[lc].ss + t[rc].ss;
    }
    inline pair<int, int> combine(pair<int, int> a, pair<int, int> b) {
        return {max(a.ff, b.ff), a.ss + b.ss};
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n].ff = a[b];
            t[n].ss = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd1(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n].ss = x;
            t[n].ff = x;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd1(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd1(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    void upd2(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, int x) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) {
            if(t[n].ff < x) return;
        }
        if(b == e && b >= i && b <= j) {
        	t[n].ss %= x;
        	t[n].ff = t[n].ss;
        	return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd2(lc, b, mid, i, j, x);
        upd2(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    pair<int, int> query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return {-LLONG_MAX, 0};
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		cin >> a[i];
	}
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	while(m--) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if(x == 1) {
			int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
			cout << t.query(1, 1, n, l, r).ss << '\n';
		}
		else if(x == 2) {
			int l, r, v; cin >> l >> r >> v;
			t.upd2(1, 1, n, l, r, v);
		}
		else {
			int i, v; cin >> i >> v;
			t.upd1(1, 1, n, i, v);
		}
	}
}

	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);

15. Problem O

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	int t[4 * N], lazy[4 * N];
	ST() {
		memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
		memset(lazy, 0, sizeof lazy);
	}
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) {
		if(lazy[n] == 0) return;
		t[n] |= lazy[n];
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] |= lazy[n];
			lazy[rc] |= lazy[n];
		}
		lazy[n] = 0;
	}
	inline int combine(int a,int b) {
	 	return a & b;
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = t[lc] & t[rc];
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = 0;
		if (b == e) {
			t[n] = 0;
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, int p) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] = p;
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j, p);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, p);
		pull(n);
	}
	int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return (1 << 30) - 1;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
	int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	vector<pair<pair<int, int>, int>> queries;
	while(m--) {
		int x, y, p;
		cin >> x >> y >> p;
		t.upd(1, 1, n, x, y, p);
		queries.push_back({{x, y}, p});
	}
	bool nope = false;
	for(auto x: queries) {
		if(t.query(1, 1, n, x.ff.ff, x.ff.ss) != x.ss) {
			nope = true;
			break;
		}
	}
	if(nope) {
		cout << "NO" << '\n';
		return;
	}
	vector<int> ans;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		ans.push_back(t.query(1, 1, n, i, i));
	}
	cout << "YES" << '\n';
	for(auto x: ans) cout << x << ' ';
	cout << '\n';
}

	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);

return 0;

16. Problem P

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct Node {
	Node() {
		g = 0, cnt = 0;
	}
	int g, cnt;
};

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    Node t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) { // Change this
    	t[n].cnt = 0;
    	t[n].g = __gcd(t[lc].g, t[rc].g);
        if(t[rc].g % t[lc].g == 0) {
        	t[n].cnt += t[lc].cnt;
        }
        if(t[lc].g % t[rc].g == 0) {
        	t[n].cnt += t[rc].cnt;
        }
    }
    inline Node combine(Node a, Node b) {
    	Node c;
        c.cnt = 0;
    	c.g = __gcd(a.g, b.g);
    	if(a.g == 0 && b.g == 0) return c;
    	if(a.g == 0) return b;
    	if(b.g == 0) return a;
        if(b.g % a.g == 0) {
        	c.cnt += a.cnt;
        }
        if(a.g % b.g == 0) {
        	c.cnt += b.cnt;
        }
        return c;
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n].g = a[b];
            t[n].cnt = 1;
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        build(lc, b, mid);
        build(rc, mid + 1, e);
        pull(n);
    }
    Node query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return Node();
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
    }
}t;

void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
	t.build(1, 1, n);
	int m; cin >> m;
	while(m--) {
		int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
		cout << (r - l + 1) - t.query(1, 1, n, l, r).cnt << '\n';
	}	
}

int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> tt;
    while(tt--) {

return 0;

		cnt[v[i]] += 1;
		fc.push_back(cnt[v[i]]);

#define int ll

    int t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = a[b];
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
        build(l, b, mid);
        build(r, mid + 1, e);
        t[n] = t[l] + t[r];
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = x;
            return;

        upd(l, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(r, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        t[n] = t[l] + t[r];
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0; 
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
        return query(l, b, mid, i, j) + query(r, mid + 1, e, i, j);

CF edu 4.1 C. Number of Minimums on a Segment

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
    pair<int, int> t[4 * N];
    static const int inf = 1e9;
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    void build(int n, int b, int e) {
        if(b == e) {
            t[n] = {a[b], 1};
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
        build(l, b, mid);
        build(r, mid + 1, e);
        if(t[l].ff < t[r].ff) {
        	t[n] = t[l];
        }
        else if(t[l].ff == t[r].ff) {
        	t[n] = {t[l].ff, t[l].ss + t[r].ss};
        }
        else {
        	t[n] = t[r];
        }
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = {x, 1};
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
        upd(l, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(r, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        if(t[l].ff < t[r].ff) {
        	t[n] = t[l];
        }
        else if(t[l].ff == t[r].ff) {
        	t[n] = {t[l].ff, t[l].ss + t[r].ss};
        }
        else {
        	t[n] = t[r];
        }
    }
    pair<int, int> query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return {INT_MAX, 0}; 
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
        pair<int, int> q1 = query(l, b, mid, i, j);
        pair<int, int> q2 = query(r, mid + 1, e, i, j);
        if(q1.ff < q2.ff) {
        	return q1;
        }
        else if(q1.ff == q2.ff) {
        	return {q1.ff, q1.ss + q2.ss};
        }
        else {
        	return q2;
        }
    }
}t;


void solve() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
    for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++) cin >> a[i];
   	t.build(1, 1, n);
    while(m--) {
    	int x, l, r;
    	cin >> x >> l >> r;
    	if(x == 1) {
    		t.upd(1, 1, n, l + 1, r);
    	}
    	else {
    		pair<int, int> p = t.query(1, 1, n, l + 1, r);
    		cout << p.ff << ' ' << p.ss << '\n';
    	}
    }
}


int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> t;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

#define ss second

ll mulmod(ll a, ll b, ll m) {
  return ((a % m) * (b % m)) % m;
}

int a[N];

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	ll t[4 * N], lazy[4 * N];

		memset(t, 0, sizeof lazy);

		t[n] = mulmod(t[n], lazy[n], mod);
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] = mulmod(lazy[lc], lazy[n], mod);
			lazy[rc] = mulmod(lazy[rc], lazy[n], mod);
		}

	}
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) { 
		if (lazy[n] == -1) return;
		t[n] = lazy[n];
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] = lazy[n];
			lazy[rc] = lazy[n];
		}
		lazy[n] = -1;
	}
	inline int combine(int a, int b) { 
	 	return min(a, b);
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = min(t[lc], t[rc]);
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = -1;
		if (b == e) {
			t[n] = 0;
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, int v) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] = v; 
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j, v);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, v);
		pull(n);
	}
	int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return INT_MAX;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
   	t.build(1, 1, n);
    while(m--) {
    	int x; cin >> x;
    	if(x == 1) {
    		int l, r, v; cin >> l >> r >> v;
    		t.upd(1, 1, n, l + 1, r, v);
    	}
    	else {
    		int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
    		cout << t.query(1, 1, n, l + 1, r) << '\n';
    	}
    }
}


int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> t;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ff first
#define ss second
#define int long long

const int N = 1e5 + 9;

int a[N];

struct ST {
	#define lc (n << 1)
	#define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
	int t[4 * N], lazy[4 * N];
	ST() {
		memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
		memset(lazy, 0, sizeof lazy);
	}
	inline void push(int n, int b, int e) { 
		if (lazy[n] == -1) return;
		t[n] = lazy[n] * (e - b + 1);
		if (b != e) {
			lazy[lc] = lazy[n];
			lazy[rc] = lazy[n];
		}
		lazy[n] = -1;
	}
	inline int combine(int a, int b) { 
	 	return a + b;
	}
	inline void pull(int n) {
	 	t[n] = t[lc] + t[rc];
	}
	void build(int n, int b, int e) {
		lazy[n] = -1;
		if (b == e) {
			t[n] = 0;
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		build(lc, b, mid);
		build(rc, mid + 1, e);
		pull(n);
	}
	void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j, int v) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (j < b || e < i) return;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) {
			lazy[n] = v; 
			push(n, b, e);
			return;
		}
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		upd(lc, b, mid, i, j, v);
		upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j, v);
		pull(n);
	}
	int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
		push(n, b, e);
		if (i > e || b > j) return 0;
		if (i <= b && e <= j) return t[n];  
		int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
		return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j));
	}
}t;

void solve() {
    int n, m;
    cin >> n >> m;
   	t.build(1, 1, n);
    while(m--) {
    	int x; cin >> x;
    	if(x == 1) {
    		int l, r, v; cin >> l >> r >> v;
    		t.upd(1, 1, n, l + 1, r, v);
    	}
    	else {
    		int l, r; cin >> l >> r;
    		cout << t.query(1, 1, n, l + 1, r) << '\n';
    	}
    }
}


int32_t main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int tt = 1;
    // cin >> t;
    while(tt--) {
    	solve();
    }

return 0;
}
